text.section:
In determining whether to transfer jurisdiction under subsection (a) of this section, the court shall consider:
the age of the child;
the mental and physical condition of the child;
the amenability of the child to treatment in an institution, facility, or program available to delinquent children;
the nature of the child's acts as proven in the trial or admitted to in a plea entered under Maryland Rule 4-242; and
public safety.
